        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Next Question is Correct",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "333 Statics learners, 574 Algebra2005 Learners, 1146 Bridge2006 learners, 4918 NIPS34 learners",
          "Algebra, Statics, Mathematics",
          "Question and Response Sequences, Knowledge Components, Difficulty",
          "[Knowledge Components, Question Sequences, Responses]",
          "Most state-of-the-art knowledge tracing approaches, especially the ones based on attention modules are problematic when it comes to handling smaller sequences → cold-start problem. ",
          "The authors propose an approach that makes KT more effective especially when dealing with smaller sequences.\n\nThis is achieved via 2 different mechanisms: \n\n1. Cone attention which converts the representation of knowledge components into an hyperbolic space.\n\n2. A Kernel bias: a logarithmic-decay based positional encoder. This ensures that more recent questions become more important than older ones. This allows working with smaller sequences because the importance of larger (older) sequences becomes diminished.",
          "Preprocessing involves the construction of sequences and the formulation of the kernel bias.\n\nMaximum sequence length is defined to be 20 questions.",
          "DKT, DKT+, DKVMN, EERNN, ATKT, SAKT, LPKT, AKT, AT-DKT, sparse-KT, FoLiBiKT, simpleKT, Dtransformer, HD-KT, csKT",
          "5-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "Statics\n{AUC: 0.8265 - csKT-50, Accuracy: 0.7990 - csKT-50}\n\nAlgebra 2005\n{AUC: 0.8213 - csKT-50, Accuracy: 0.8077 - DKT-500}\n\nBD2006\n{AUC:  0.8094 - csKT-50, Accuracy: 0.8555 - csKT-50}\n\nStatics\n{AUC: 0.7985 - csKT-50 & csKT-100, Accuracy: 0.7284 - csKT-50}",
          "Author attempt different predictions using different sequence lengths - 50, 100 and 500 questions under a cold-start scenario.\n\nResults show that the approach using the kernel bias assigns more importance to more recent questions, which makes it more effective than state-of-the-art techniques.\n\nAuthors also perform ablation studies to see effectiveness of the different modules of the arquitecture.",
          "Only tests model performance under the cold-start scenario.\n\nModel only considers answer sequences, not accounting for other potentially predictive factors such as engagement.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
