    {
      "id": "18d4750c-f3ba-804c-9a99-fb1f8e837bbe",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors propose csKT, which is meant to be able to be trained on small sequences and then expand in a smoother way to longer sequences. This is done via a kernel bias and cone attention.",
